\pard\sb280\sa120\cf4\b\fs26 5.2 Candidate Nomination Workflow\par

\pard 
{\pntext\f0 1.\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnindent360\pnstart1\pndec{\pntxta.}}
\fi-280\li560\sa80\cf3\b0\fs21 Electoral Officer opens nomination period with a configurable form.\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}\cf3\fs21 Students submit: full name, photo (max 2MB), manifesto (PDF, max 5MB), optional video link, contact info.\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f0 3.\tab}\cf3\fs21 Electoral Officer reviews each submission \f2\emdash\f0  Approve, Reject (with reason), or Request Revision.\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f0 4.\tab}\cf3\fs21 Approved candidates are notified by SMS/email. Their profile is published on the voting portal.\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f0 5.\tab}\cf3\fs21 Nomination period closes. Candidate list is locked. No further additions allowed.\cf0\fs22\par

\pard\sa80\par

\pard\sb280\sa120\cf4\b\fs26 5.3 Voter Eligibility Engine\par

\pard\sa140\sl360\slmult1\cf3\b0\fs22 Eligibility is defined per election and enforced at vote-cast time, not just display time. The system cross-checks four factors:\cf0\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-280\li560\sa80\cf3\fs21 Institutional enrollment status (active student only)\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\cf3\fs21 Department membership (must be in an eligible department)\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\cf3\fs21 Year level (e.g. 3rd year+ only for certain positions)\cf0\fs22\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\cf3\fs21 No prior vote cast in this election (one-vote-per-student-per-position enforcement)\cf0\fs22\par

